race.comment: Wide open and very tough finish to the day. The pattern will be key with SUNSHINEINMYPOCKET (3) who goes on top, a touch hesitantly it must be said. He's certainly good enough and was very unlucky two back before a good effort in very fast time at Flemington behind Persian Spirit who was heavily backed and should've won a Listed race last week. SUNSHINEINMYPOCKET's pattern from a wide draw here will make it tough but with a good ride he can be too strong late. STYLISH (10) was first up off a short break at Caulfield and found the line nicely to grab third. We'll get a guide to that form earlier with Dark Simba & Somewhere. She can land much closer from the good gate here and take beating. ROADCONE (14) has been solid in two runs back, also through the Taken race last time. He lands on speed and can take catching. HE'LL RIP (13) continues to race in good form, second to Sabaj last time over 1600m reading very well. No issue back in trip.
